New Records: Matthew Short took his maiden professional five-for.
Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone scored 87 off 47 deliveries, including five sixes and six fours.
Matthew Short took a five-wicket haul, including the crucial wickets of Livingstone and Carse.
Adil Rashid steered England to victory with a single.
Jake Fraser-McGurk scored his first international fifty.
Brydon Carse impressed with a couple of wickets and a 91mph delivery.
England won by three wickets with six balls to spare.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Brydon Carse returned to cricket after a three-month ban for breaching betting regulations.
Adil Rashid and Brydon Carse put the brakes on Australia's scoring after the powerplay.
Sam Curran's pace-off delivery dismissed Josh Inglis.
Will Jacks and Jordan Cox were dismissed by Sean Abbott in quick succession.
Livingstone survived a review for lbw in an eventful over.
Jacob Bethell took down Australia's premier spinner Adam Zampa.
